docs.snippet: MONTEVIDEO, April 20. -- With the adoption of the new Constitution this week, Uruguay's "third republic" begins life with another set of striking innovations in constitutional law. They will maintain the country's reputation as a laboratory for...
docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEVIDEO, April 20. -- With the adoption of the new Constitution this week, Uruguay's "third republic" begins life with another set of striking innovations in constitutional law. They will maintain the country's reputation as a laboratory for interesting social, political and governmental experimentation.

headline.main: URUGUAY LAUNCHES 'THIRD REPUBLIC'; New Constitution Provides for Vast Experiment With Parliamentary System. RESPONSIBILITY CENTRED Cabinet Will Originate Revenue Bills -- Censure to Apply to Members as Individuals.

byline.original: By JOHN W. WHITE.Special Cable to THE NEW YORK TIMES
